  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Arthrodesis to the sacroiliac joint and symphysis</intervention_name>
    <description>Standard surgical procedures will be used. When the patient has isolated pain in the symphysis isolated fixation will be performed. A 2x2 cm large bone block will be removed and replaced with spongy bone. For fixation the Matta-plate will be applied.
To the sacroiliac joint we use an anterior approach. A 2x1,5 cm large bone block will be removed and replaced with spongy bone from the iliac crest. For joint fixation we either use 2 plates or sacroiliac screws. The same procedure will be used on the other side in the cases with bilateral symptoms. Only one side will be operated at a time. After one year it will be decided if it's necessary to perform contralateral surgery.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Sacroilliac fusion</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
